---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  pageHeading="Quick Start Checklist"
  description="You already know Meshtastic. Here's the KC-specific config and five steps to verify you're on the mesh."
  heroVariant="compact"
>
  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">
      Quick start for people who already know Meshtastic
    </h2>
    <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
      You've deployed before. You don't need hand-holding. Here's the KC mesh config and verification steps. Takes 10 minutes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- KC Mesh Settings -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-blue/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue/5 to-kc-sky/10 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-kc-sky/20 dark:from-kc-blue/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Kansas City mesh configuration</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Region</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-lg text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">United States (915 MHz)</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Preset</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-lg text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">LongFast (SF11, 125 kHz BW)</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Channel</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-lg text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">LongFast default (public)</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">Hop Limit</div>
        <div class="mt-2 text-lg text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">3 (default)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 rounded-xl bg-kc-blue/5 border border-kc-blue/20 p-5 dark:bg-kc-sky/5 dark:border-kc-sky/20">
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <strong>That's it for basic config.</strong> Match these settings to join the KC mesh. Add private channels on top if needed, but primary channel should be compatible with these values.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 5-Step Checklist -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Five-step deployment checklist</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-kc-blue text-cream-50 font-bold dark:bg-kc-sky dark:text-ink-900">1</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Flash firmware (if needed)</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">Use latest stable Meshtastic firmware. <a href="https://flasher.meshtastic.org" class="text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">flasher.meshtastic.org</a> is easiest. Verify device boots and shows startup screen.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-kc-blue text-cream-50 font-bold dark:bg-kc-sky dark:text-ink-900">2</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Pair via Bluetooth</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">Open Meshtastic app (iOS/Android). Add device via Bluetooth. PIN usually "123456" or shown on screen. Connection takes 10-30 seconds.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-kc-blue text-cream-50 font-bold dark:bg-kc-sky dark:text-ink-900">3</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Apply KC mesh settings</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">Set Region: US (915 MHz). Set Preset: LongFast. Set device role (CLIENT for mobile, ROUTER for fixed infrastructure). Name your node (KC-YourName recommended).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-kc-blue text-cream-50 font-bold dark:bg-kc-sky dark:text-ink-900">4</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Set location (optional but helpful)</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">GPS devices auto-populate. Manual: set approximate location (within 1 mile for privacy is fine). Helps with network planning and node discovery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border-2 border-mesh-green/30 bg-mesh-green/5 p-6 dark:border-mesh-green/20 dark:bg-mesh-green/10">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-mesh-green text-ink-900 font-bold">5</div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-mesh-green">Verify you're on the mesh</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">Check "Nodes" tab in app. If you see Router 1 (east side) or other KC nodes, you're connected. If you see 0 nodes but you're in coverage area, check region setting (most common error).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Role-Specific Config -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Role-specific configuration notes</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">CLIENT (mobile/handheld)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• Device Role: CLIENT</li>
          <li>• TX Power: 10-20 dBm</li>
          <li>• Smart Position: Enabled</li>
          <li>• Screen timeout: Short (battery saving)</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">ROUTER (fixed infrastructure)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• Device Role: ROUTER</li>
          <li>• TX Power: 20-30 dBm</li>
          <li>• Position: Fixed location</li>
          <li>• Power: Solar or AC (continuous)</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-kc-blue dark:text-kc-sky">ROUTER_CLIENT (hybrid)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          <li>• Device Role: ROUTER_CLIENT</li>
          <li>• TX Power: 15-25 dBm</li>
          <li>• Routes when stationary</li>
          <li>• Good for semi-mobile setups</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <a href="/guides/router-gateway" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Full router vs gateway configuration guide →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Coverage Check -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Coverage verification</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>Router 1 (east side) is operational.</strong> If you're within 5-8 miles of east KC / Raytown area, you should see it.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Router 2 (west side) is not yet deployed.</strong> Johnson County, Overland Park, western KC currently has minimal coverage. That's the priority gap I'm trying to close.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>See 0 nodes but you know you're in range?</strong> Check region setting first (US, not EU). Then verify LongFast preset. Then check antenna connection.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a href="/network/coverage" class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Check coverage map →
      </a>
      <a href="/guides/west-side" class="inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
        Help deploy Router 2 (west side) →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Anti-Dogma Quick Tips -->
  <section class="mt-12 rounded-3xl border-2 border-kc-red/30 bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-red/5 to-sunset-amber/5 p-6 sm:p-8 dark:border-sunset-amber/20 dark:from-kc-red/10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-kc-red dark:text-sunset-amber">Deployment reality check (anti-dogma)</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        <strong>If you're coming from online forums, forget what they told you about perfection.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <div class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">❌ Forums say: "Need 40-foot tower"</div>
        <div class="mt-1">✓ Reality: Router 1 runs at 15 feet, covers 5-8 miles</div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <div class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">❌ Forums say: "50W solar minimum"</div>
        <div class="mt-1">✓ Reality: 10W works fine in KC, running for months</div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <div class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">❌ Forums say: "Indoor nodes useless"</div>
        <div class="mt-1">✓ Reality: Test your building, some work 1-3 miles</div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
        <div class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">❌ Forums say: "Must have vertical polarization"</div>
        <div class="mt-1">✓ Reality: Horizontal works with 3-6 dB penalty (test it)</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <a href="/guides/solar-residential" class="text-base font-medium text-kc-red hover:text-kc-blue dark:text-sunset-amber dark:hover:text-kc-sky">
        Full anti-dogma deployment guide →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Optimization Next Steps -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">After you're connected: optimization</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Test elevation impact</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Move your node to different heights. Track how many nodes you see and SNR. Even 6-10 feet makes a difference. Find what works for your location.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Consider better antenna</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Stock antennas work. Better 5-8 dBi outdoor antenna ($20-40) dramatically improves range if you decide to optimize later.
        </p>
        <a href="/get-started/hardware" class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          Hardware guide →
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-border-light bg-surface-100 p-6 dark:border-border-dark dark:bg-sand-900">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-cream-50">Add solar for permanent deployment</h3>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-ink-700 dark:text-cream-100">
          Running on battery now? 10W solar + 10Ah battery ($50-75) lets you deploy permanently outdoors without power cables.
        </p>
        <a href="/guides/solar-residential" class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-kc-blue hover:text-kc-red dark:text-kc-sky dark:hover:text-sunset-amber">
          Solar setup guide →
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Done -->
  <section class="mt-12 text-center">
    <div class="inline-block rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-kc-blue to-kc-red p-8 text-cream-50 shadow-card md:p-10">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold">You're on the KC mesh</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-base opacity-95">
        Configured correctly? Seeing other nodes? That's it. You're done. Now go deploy more infrastructure.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="/network/coverage"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-kc-blue transition hover:bg-surface-200"
        >
          Coverage Map
        </a>
        <a
          href="/guides/west-side"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-cream-50 px-6 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-cream-50 transition hover:bg-cream-50 hover:text-kc-blue"
        >
          Help Deploy Router 2
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
